handist.collections

Class SquareRange

  • java.lang.Object
    • handist.collections.SquareRange
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class SquareRange
extends Object
implements Serializable
    Class SquareRange describes an interval over long values.

    The lower bound is included and the upper bound is excluded from the interval, meaning that for two long values a and b (a<b), all the long values l such that a ≤ l < b are contained within the SquareRange [a,b).

    It is possible to create "empty" SquareRange instances where the lower bound is equal to the upper bound. In this case it is considered that there are no long values included in the SquareRange.

      • isOverlapped

        public boolean isOverlapped(SquareRange range)
        Returns true if the provided SquareRange and this instance are overlapped. This operation is symmetric, meaning that calling this method with two instances a and b, the result produced by a.isOverlapped(b) is the same as b.isOverlapped(a).

        Two SquareRange a and b are overlapped if they share some indices, that is if there exist a long l such that a.contains(l) and b.contains(l) return true.

        In cases where an empty SquareRange and a non-empty SquareRange are considered, this method returns true if the lower bound (or upper bound as it has the same value) of the empty instance is between the lower bound (included) and the upper bound (excluded) of the other instance.

        If both considered SquareRange are empty, returns true if they have the same bounds.

        Parameters:
        range - the range whose overlap with this instance is to be checked
        Returns:
        true if the provided LongRange and this instance overlap
